claim.claim-text:
1. A food product breading machine comprising:
a breading reservoir having side walls, a lower wall that spans between the side walls and slopes upwardly at one end, an end wall adjacent an upper end of said sloping wall, and an upper wall spaced from said end wall to provide an opening through which breading material is dispensed from the reservoir;
a breading conveyor comprising a conveyor belt disposed in said reservoir with a first conveyor run extending generally horizontally along said upper reservoir wall, and a second conveyor run extending along said sloping lower wall, said conveyor moving breading material in said reservoir along said sloping lower wall toward said end wall for delivery to a breading station above said upper wall;
a drive roller mounted by support bearings to the reservoir for moving the conveyor belt; and
a drive transmission for applying a torque to said drive roller, said transmission including a shaft mounting by shaft bearings for providing motive power to the drive roller; and a latch for securing the drive roller and transmission shaft in side to side relation to each other and for bearing a weight of said reservoir to reduce wear on the transmission shaft and shaft bearings.

3. A food product breading machine comprising:
a breading reservoir having side walls, a lower wall that spans between the side walls and slopes upwardly at one end, an end wall adjacent an upper end of said Sloping wall, and an upper wall spaced from said end wall to provide an opening through which breading material is dispensed from the reservoir;
a breading conveyor comprising a conveyor belt disposed in said reservoir with a first conveyor run extending generally horizontally along said upper reservoir wall, and a second conveyor run extending along said sloping lower wall, said conveyor moving breading material in said reservoir along said sloping lower wall toward said end wall for delivery to a breading station above said upper wall;
a plurality of breading material flow restrictors for contacting food product coated with breading material at the breading station;
a drive roller mounted by support bearings to the reservoir for moving the conveyor belt; and
a drive transmission for applying a torque to said drive roller;
said upper wail having a length L which extends from the opening through which the breading material moves past a region of the breading flow restrictors at the breading station along the first run of said conveyor and wherein the upper wall comprises a flat metal surface positioned beneath the belt of the conveyor and has flanges extending downward into the reservoir for engagement with side walls of the reservoir and wherein threaded mounting studs are attached to the flanges for attaching the upper wall to said side walls.

4. A food product breading machine comprising:
a breading reservoir having side walls, a lower wall that spans between the side walls and slopes upwardly at one end, an end wall adjacent an upper end of said sloping wall, and an upper wall spaced from said end wall to provide an opening through which breading material is dispensed from the reservoir;
a breading conveyor comprising a conveyor belt disposed in said reservoir with a first conveyor run extending generally horizontally along said upper reservoir wall, and a second conveyor run extending along said sloping lower wall, said conveyor moving breading material in said reservoir along said sloping lower wall toward said end wall for delivery to a breading station above said upper wall;
a plurality of breading material flow restrictors for contacting food product coated with breading material at the breading station;
a drive roller mounted by support bearings to the reservoir for moving the conveyor belt; and
a drive transmission for applying a torque to said drive roller;
said upper wall having a length L which extends from the opening through which the breading material moves past a region of the breading flow restrictors at the breading station along the first run of said conveyor and wherein the upper wall comprises a flat metal surface positioned beneath the belt of the conveyor and has flanges extending downward into the reservoir for engagement with side walls of the reservoir and wherein threaded mounting studs are attached to the flanges for attaching the upper wall to said side walls and further the upper wall has a rear section extending back toward the opening through which breading material is conveyed from the reservoir and a front section extending forward toward a discharge region where food product drops from the conveyor first run, said rear section extending beyond a rear mounting stud an adjustable distance depending on the breading material and food product and said forward section extending forward of a front mounting stud an adjustable distance depending on the breading material and the food product.

5. A food product breading machine comprising:
a breading reservoir having side walls, a lower wall that spans between the side walls and slopes upwardly at one end, an end wall adjacent an upper end of said sloping wall, and an upper wall spaced from said end wall to provide an opening through which breading material is dispensed from the reservoir;
a breading conveyor comprising a conveyor belt disposed in said reservoir with a first conveyor run extending generally horizontally along said upper reservoir wall, and a second conveyor run extending along said sloping lower wall, said conveyor moving breading material in said reservoir along said sloping lower wall toward said end wall for delivery to a breading station above said upper wall;
a plurality of breading material flow restrictors for contacting food product coated with breading material at the breading station;
a drive roller mounted by support bearings to the reservoir for moving the conveyor belt; and
a drive transmission for applying a torque to said drive roller;
said upper wall having a length L which extends from the opening through which the breading material moves past a region of the breading flow restrictors at the breading station along the first run of said conveyor and wherein the upper wall has a rear section extending back toward the opening through which breading material is conveyed from the reservoir and a front section extending forward toward a discharge region where food product drops from the conveyor first run, said rear section extending beyond a rear mounting stud an adjustable distance depending on the breading material and food product and said forward section extending forward of a front mounting stud an adjustable distance depending on the breading material and the food product.
